menu "Vcore-collapse watchdog (TA-318)"

    config TM_VCORE_WATCHDOG
        bool "Enable vcore-collapse watchdog (bb_power_health)"
        default n
        help
            Monitor the TPS546 vcore rail every 5 s using bb_vcore_wd_eval().
            On BB_VCORE_WD_RECOVER: increment NVS burst counter and esp_restart()
            to clear a latched OC/UV fault without a physical power-cycle.
            On BB_VCORE_WD_BACKOFF: log and hold (burst limit reached).
            Bitaxe (ASIC) boards only — enabled via sdkconfig/bitaxe-*. The
            asic_task.c watchdog glue is additionally gated by #ifdef ASIC_CHIP,
            so it is a no-op on non-ASIC builds even if this is forced on.
            NOTE: ASIC_BM1368/ASIC_BM1370 are C preprocessor build-flag defines,
            not Kconfig symbols, so a `depends on` cannot gate on them (Kconfig
            treats undefined symbols as n, which silently compiled the watchdog
            OUT on every board — the original TA-318 bug). Gate per-board in
            sdkconfig instead.

endmenu

menu "TPS546 VIN UVLO thresholds"

    config TM_TPS546_VIN_ON_MV
        int "TPS546 VIN_ON threshold (mV)"
        range 3500 18000
        default 4400
        help
            TPS546 VIN_ON (turn-on) threshold in mV. The regulator enables when VIN rises above
            this. Relaxed from AxeOS 4800 to tolerate non-OEM/sagging supplies (ESP-Miner #1188).
            Set just above VIN_OFF for hysteresis. Note the TPS546's rated minimum input is ~4.5V;
            values below that trade spec-margin for transient-sag tolerance.

    config TM_TPS546_VIN_OFF_MV
        int "TPS546 VIN_OFF threshold (mV)"
        range 3500 18000
        default 4200
        help
            TPS546 VIN_OFF (turn-off / UVLO) threshold in mV. The regulator shuts off when VIN
            sags below this. Relaxed from AxeOS 4500, which false-trips and latches on supplies
            that droop under load (#1188). Tune ~0.3-0.5V below the rail voltage measured at the
            miner under full load.

endmenu
